<p>Solar panels in San Francisco typically achieve payback periods of 6-7 years due to the city's high electricity rates of 31.8¬¢/kWh. A typical 6kW system costing \$14,700 after the federal tax credit can generate annual savings of approximately \$2,290, leading to over \$57,000 in total savings over 25 years. The return on investment is enhanced by San Francisco's net energy metering program, which credits excess solar production at full retail rates. Property value increases of 3-4% are common with solar installations in San Francisco's competitive real estate market. With PG&E's time-of-use rates, solar systems that include battery storage can provide even greater savings by storing solar energy for use during peak rate periods. Over the 25-year warranted life of solar panels, San Francisco homeowners typically see total returns of 300-400% on their initial investment, making solar one of the best long-term home improvements available.</p>

